To install Node Version Manager (NVM) and then use it to install Node.js version 22, follow these steps:

Step 1: Install NVM
Run the following command to download and install NVM (Node Version Manager):
  curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.3/install.sh
  curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.3/install.sh | bash

Step 2: Load NVM
After installation, load NVM into your shell by running the following command:
  source ~/. rc
This ensures that NVM is available in your terminal session.

Step 3: Install Node.js version 22 using NVM
Now, you can install Node.js version 22 by running:
  nvm install 22
This will download and install Node.js version 22.

Step 4: Verify the installation
Once the installation is complete, verify the installed Node.js version:
  node -v
